import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['speed'].hist(bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed across all locations?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], c=data['dir'], cmap='hsv')
    plt.title('How does wind direction vary across different locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['dirCat'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common wind direction category across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['dir'] = data['dir'].astype(float)
    data['speed'] = data['speed'].astype(float)
    plt.scatter(data['dir'], data['speed'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('How does wind speed vary with wind direction?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Direction')
    plt.ylabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
